Eugene.Ya Po Ah Terrace:
Ya-Po-Ah Terrace (nickname The High Place), is the tallest building in Downtown Eugene, Oregon at 212 feet (65 m). It is a controversial high-rise apartment building for senior citizens erected at the foot of the butte in 1968.


== History ==
"Ya Po Ah" means very high place in the language of the Kalapuya Indians who inhabited the Willamette Valley prior to the arrival of the Euro-American settlers.
